<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870811-0057 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:Quaker Oats Co.</HL><DD> 08/11/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> OAT FBCTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><TEXT>   Quaker Oats Co., Chicago, said it sold its Houston-based Igloo Products Corp. unit to a group of investors that includes management and First Boston Corp., a New York-based investment bank. Terms weren't disclosed, but analysts have estimated Igloo's value at about $100 million.    Igloo, a maker of ice chests and beverage coolers, was acquired by Quaker last September when it paid $805 million for Anderson, Clayton andamp; Co.    Quaker, a food and consumer products concern, has said it wants to sell everything it acquired in the Anderson Clayton transaction except for the Gaines pet food unit. </TEXT></DOC>